<h1>Obtaining and Building HPCToolkit Software</h1>

<h2><a href="software-instructions.html">Prerequisites &amp; Instructions</a></h2>



<h2>Source code for HPCToolkit</h2>

To build HPCToolkit from source, you need to download and build both hpctoolkit and hpctoolkit-externals.
<ul>
  <table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="2" border="1" width="100%">

  <tr>
  <td><a href="https://code.google.com/p/hpctoolkit/source/browse/#svn%2Ftrunk">hpctoolkit</a>
  </td>
  <td><code>svn co http://hpctoolkit.googlecode.com/svn/trunk hpctoolkit</code>
  </td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
  <td><a href="https://code.google.com/p/hpctoolkit/source/browse/#svn%2Fexternals">hpctoolkit-externals</a>
  </td>
  <td><code>svn co http://hpctoolkit.googlecode.com/svn/externals hpctoolkit-externals</code>
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>
</ul>

<h2>Binary releases for HPCToolkit GUI interfaces (recommended for tool users)</h2>


Due to the difficulty of building the hpcviewer and hpctraceviewer graphical user interfaces from source using 
Eclipse, we provide binary releases for these tools. 
